  "notes": "Maltese, the only Semitic language written in the Latin script and official EU language. Evolved from Siculo-Arabic. Digraph għ represents pharyngeal fricative, h is silent. Ċ and ġ are retroflex-palatal affricates. Extensive lexical borrowing from Sicilian/Italian and English.",
